<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND
        CRANKCASE - DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT AND MAIN BEARINGS (RECONDITIONING) - VISCOUS VIBRATION DAMPER AND PULLEY
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="2">
        <title>VISCOUS VIBRATION DAMPER AND PULLEY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the vibration damper as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Loosen and remove the six capscrews (
                    <emph type="bold">1, Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150733">7.33</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ) and hardened washers which secure the viscous damper to the crankshaft pulley and remove the
                    damper.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove the capscrews (
                    <emph type="bold">2, Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150733">7.33</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ) with the retainer plate securing the crankshaft pulley to the crankshaft, as shown.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Install a universal puller using 3/8 in. bolts long enough to hold the puller in place.
                    Turn the forcing screw and remove the pulley. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150734">7.34</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <figure id="ef4150733" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg5981" filename="../figcg5/CG5981.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.33. Viscous Vibration Damper.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">1. Vibration Damper Capscrews</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">2. Retainer Plate Cap Screws</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4150734" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11607" filename="../figcg1/CG11607.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.34. Remove Pulley.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
